With reference to the goal definitions in “Goal Definitions” section, different study contexts explore different questions, and will arrive at different answers in relation to the quantity of storage required. Approaches (1), (4) and (5) do not consider system-level implications at all, and therefore do not consider storage. Approach (2) specifically assumes that ‘PV plus storage’ substitutes for dispatchable generation, and therefore requires solar overbuild and substantial storage. Weißbach et al. (2013, p. 213) adopted a 2-time solar PV overbuild, resulting in a halving of EROI. The EROI was reduced by a further ∼\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
