6b
System lifetime
20–30 years
Studies take into account manufacturers’ expectations and historic experience. 85% of the current installed global PV capacity is less than five years old (Meydbray and Dross 2016). Future performance is uncertain. An increase from 20 to 30 years reduces EPBT 33% (increases EROI 50%)

